    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-08T10:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-08T10:30:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-08T12:00:00-03:30"
                            >September 8, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 8—11:09
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Government organ <hi rend="italic">El Pueblo</hi> publishes note from
                    Uruguayan Minister for Foreign Affairs to Uruguayan Minister to Paris dated
                    August 28 acknowledging thanks of Alcalá Zamora<note n="67" xml:id="d471fn67"
                        >Niceto Alcala Zamora, President of Spanish Republic, 1931–36.</note> for
                    Uruguay’s proposed mediation, giving précis of replies received from countries
                    addressed and concluding by announcing the postponement of the negotiations
                    until more suitable opportunity. Copy of the note was transmitted to the
                    Uruguayan Minister at Washington for communication to Pan American Union with
                    recommendation that he continue the conversations privately in Washington
                    outside the official meetings of the Pan American Union in order to be ready to
                    promote the Uruguayan initiative when any opportunity is presented.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
